<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,542]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">
As the male specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Alvarado, 2018" authorityName="Alvarado" authorityYear="2018" box="[491,595,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Aphanistes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silviae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[491,595,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">A. silviae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[601,664,151,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[601,664,151,176]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
would not fit in the characterization of the species-groups unless it is related with its female, it was compared with all the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Forster" authorityYear="1869" box="[735,858,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Aphanistes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[735,858,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">Aphanistes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species occurring in the Neotropical region (except for 
<taxonomicName authority="Gauld &amp; Bradshaw, 1997" authorityName="Gauld &amp; Bradshaw" authorityYear="1997" box="[191,607,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Aphanistes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colladoi">
<emphasis box="[191,314,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">A. colladoi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gauld" box="[321,607,223,248]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" refString="Gauld, I. D. &amp; Bradshaw, K. (1997) Subfamily Anomaloninae. In: Gauld, I. D. (Ed.), The Ichneumonidae of Costa Rica. 2. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 57, pp. 1 - 485." type="journal article" year="1997">Gauld &amp; Bradshaw, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) but the differences mentioned here will allow it to be distinguished from all the species in the region. 
<taxonomicName authority="Alvarado, 2018" authorityName="Alvarado" authorityYear="2018" box="[484,689,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Aphanistes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silviae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[484,689,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">Aphanistes silviae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[699,764,260,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[699,764,260,285]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs in having the meso- and metasoma reddish brown, while the other species have the meso- and metathorax black or mesosoma black (black with margins of the sclerites reddish brown in 
<taxonomicName authority="Gauld &amp; Bradshaw, 1997" authorityName="Gauld &amp; Bradshaw" authorityYear="1997" box="[446,821,332,357]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Aphanistes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="didii">
<emphasis box="[446,528,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">A. didii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gauld" box="[536,821,332,357]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" refString="Gauld, I. D. &amp; Bradshaw, K. (1997) Subfamily Anomaloninae. In: Gauld, I. D. (Ed.), The Ichneumonidae of Costa Rica. 2. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 57, pp. 1 - 485." type="journal article" year="1997">Gauld &amp; Bradshaw, 1997</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) and metasoma dark reddish brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="234" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,151,542]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">
